Plug-in name: Impact
Plug-in shortname: impact
Description: impact analysis

Most options of the form '-impact-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-impact-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-impact-annot <f1, ..., fn>  use the impact annotations in the code of
                    functions f1,...,fn (preferably use -impact-annot="f1,
                    ..., fn")
-impact-graph       build a graph that explains why a statement is in the set
                    of impacted nodes (opposite option is -impact-no-graph)
-impact-in-callers  compute compute impact in callers as well as in callees
                    (set by default, opposite option is
                    -impact-not-in-callers)
-impact-not-in-callers  opposite of option -impact-in-callers, whose help
                    message is:
                    compute compute impact in callers as well as in callees
-impact-print       print the impacted stmt (opposite option is
                    -impact-no-print)
-impact-skip <v1,...,vn>  consider that those variables are not impacted
                    (preferably use -impact-skip="v1,...,vn")
-impact-slicing     slice from the impacted stmt (opposite option is
                    -impact-no-slicing)

*** DEBUG

-impact-debug <n>   level of debug for plug-in Impact (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-impact-help        help of plug-in Impact
-impact-h           alias for option -impact-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-impact-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Impact to a file. <K> is
                    a combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -impact-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-impact-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -impact-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -impact-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-impact-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in Impact (default to 1)
-impact-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category
                    <k1> to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -impact-warn-key help
                    to get a list of available categories, and * to enable
                    all categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -impact-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
